My first memory of trifle pudding is one of an eat-and-run mission. It was during the height of Visiting Season — the “Festive Season” to those who are not conscripted into extended family visits and enough cups of tea to trigger a Five Roses shortage. My grandmother’s living room was where we would gather for the annual Christmas Eve dinner.
 
